sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K607027
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: LasR protein with moderately fast degradation tag under transcriptional control of PlasB promoter and reverse antisense PBad promoter, the RBS has a strength of 0.07 (obtained by Jason Kelly and Robbie Bryant during the summer of 2004 using a fluorescent reporter). This construct represents (in presence of N-(3-oxododecanoyl)homoserine lactone in the media) an auto-inducing loop in which the PlasB promoter drives expression of its own inducer LasR. The running loop can be turned off through activation of the reverse antisense PBad promoter by arabinose.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Olesja Popow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_M0052
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This variation of the SsrA tag was studied by McGinness, Baker, Sauer. 2006. Mol. Cell. 22:701. SsrA tags are prevalent in E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This sequence codes for the amino acid sequence AANDENYADAS, a slower variation of the WT SsrA tag sequence, which, when fused to the C-terminal of proteins, will make the protein susceptible to moderately fast degradation through SspB-mediated binding to the ClpX protease. The following rates of degradation of this tag are pulled from the corresponding references below: ~1 Vmax/ [Clpx6] min-1 from (1).
See the following references for further information on degradation rates and mechanisms of this tag: (1)McGinness, Baker, Sauer. 2006. Mol. Cell. 22:701. (2)Flynn et al 2003. Mol. Cell. 11: 671. Flynn et al. 2001. PNAS 98(19): 10584. Anderson et al 1998. App. Env. Microbiol. 64(6):2240.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
C-terminal tag. Degradation rate is moderately fast. Variations of this sequence yield different degradation rates(see Parts BBa_M0050, BBa_M0051, BBa_M0053). Sequence derived from reverse translation of AANDENYADAS sequence using codon usage optimized for E. coli. Three C-terminal aa's (DAS in this case) are necessary and sufficient for ClpX binding and degradation. Upstream aa sequence serves as a binding site for SspB, which guides rapid binding to ClpX. See sources on the main part page for further information about the mechanism of the system.
NOTE: this sequence has only the amino acid sequence for the tag and bears NO STOP CODONS, so be sure to include them if you use this sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Felix Moser

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0031
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Medium RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-1" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS.

Contact info for this part: Brian Cho
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty
